## QuadTree.visitTileKey() method

Visits the subtree starting from the given tile.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
visitTileKey(tileKey: TileKey, accept: (tileKey: TileKey, geoBox: GeoBox) => boolean): void;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  tileKey | [TileKey](./harp-geoutils.tilekey.md) | The root of the subtree that should be visited. |
|  accept | (tileKey: [TileKey](./harp-geoutils.tilekey.md)<!-- -->, geoBox: [GeoBox](./harp-geoutils.geobox.md)<!-- -->) =&gt; boolean | A function that takes a \[\[TileKey\]\] and its bounding box in geo coordinates and returns <code>true</code> if the visit of the <code>QuadTree</code> should continue; otherwise <code>false</code>. |

<b>Returns:</b>

void
